+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ni3uMPoD97xxwAqstWTcXB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# Beam Splitter\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆBuild a beam propagation simulator for a 2D grid laboratory.\n     4ŌåÆ\n     5ŌåÆ## Grid Format\n     6ŌåÆ\n     7ŌåÆThe grid is a 2D array of single-character strings:\n     8ŌåÆ\n     9ŌåÆ- `'S'` ŌĆö beam source (always on the top row). Emits a beam straight down.\n    10ŌåÆ- `'^'` ŌĆö splitter. When a beam arrives, it splits into two diagonal beams.\n    11ŌåÆ- `'.'` ŌĆö empty cell. Beams pass through.\n    12ŌåÆ\n    13ŌåÆBeams that leave the grid boundaries are absorbed (they stop).\n    14ŌåÆ\n    15ŌåÆ## Beam Movement Rules\n    16ŌåÆ\n    17ŌåÆ1. A beam from the source `'S'` moves **straight down** (row+1, same column) each step.\n    18ŌåÆ2. When a beam hits a splitter `'^'`, it splits into **two beams**:\n    19ŌåÆ   - One goes **down-left** (row+1, col-1)\n    20ŌåÆ   - One goes **down-right** (row+1, col+1)\n    21ŌåÆ   The original beam is consumed by the splitter (it does not continue straight).\n    22ŌåÆ3. An unsplit beam (not at a splitter) continues in its current direction:\n    23ŌåÆ   - A downward beam continues downward (row+1, same col)\n    24ŌåÆ   - A down-left beam continues down-left (row+1, col-1)\n    25ŌåÆ   - A down-right beam continues down-right (row+1, col+1)\n    26ŌåÆ4. A beam is **absorbed** when it moves outside the grid boundaries (row < 0, row >= rows, col < 0, col >= cols).\n    27ŌåÆ5. Multiple beams can occupy the same cell simultaneously.\n    28ŌåÆ6. Splitters always split regardless of the beam's incoming direction.\n    29ŌåÆ\n    30ŌåÆ## API\n    31ŌåÆ\n    32ŌåÆExport two functions from `src/index.ts`:\n    33ŌåÆ\n    34ŌåÆ### `countBeamCells(grid: string[][]): number`\n    35ŌåÆ\n    36ŌåÆCount the number of distinct cells visited by any beam. A cell counts once even if multiple beams pass through it. The source cell `'S'` counts as visited. Splitter cells hit by beams count as visited.\n    37ŌåÆ\n    38ŌåÆ### `countBeamPaths(grid: string[][]): bigint`\n    39ŌåÆ\n    40ŌåÆCount the total number of distinct source-to-exit paths through the grid. Each time a beam splits at `'^'`, both branches are separate paths. A path ends when the beam exits the grid (moves beyond any edge).\n    41ŌåÆ\n    42ŌåÆWith K splitters along a beam's path, there are potentially 2^K paths. The result can be astronomically large, so return a `bigint`.\n    43ŌåÆ\n    44ŌåÆ**Performance constraint**: Must handle a 200x200 grid with up to 50 splitters and return results in under 5 seconds. Enumerating individual paths is not feasible for large inputs.\n    45ŌåÆ\n    46ŌåÆ## Example\n    47ŌåÆ\n    48ŌåÆ```\n    49ŌåÆGrid (4 rows x 5 cols):\n    50ŌåÆ. S . . .\n    51ŌåÆ. . . . .\n    52ŌåÆ. ^ . . .\n    53ŌåÆ. . . . .\n    54ŌåÆ```\n    55ŌåÆ\n    56ŌåÆ- The beam starts at (0,1) where `'S'` is.\n    57ŌåÆ- It moves down: (1,1), (2,1) ŌĆö hits splitter.\n    58ŌåÆ- Splits into down-left (3,0) and down-right (3,2).\n    59ŌåÆ- Both beams exit the grid after row 3.\n    60ŌåÆ- Visited cells: (0,1), (1,1), (2,1), (3,0), (3,2) ŌåÆ `countBeamCells` returns **5**.\n    61ŌåÆ- Paths: 2 distinct paths (one ending at (3,0), one at (3,2)) ŌåÆ `countBeamPaths` returns **2n**.\n    62ŌåÆ\n    63ŌåÆ```\n    64ŌåÆGrid with two splitters:\n    65ŌåÆ. S . . .\n    66ŌåÆ. ^ . . .\n    67ŌåÆ^ . ^ . .\n    68ŌåÆ. . . . .\n    69ŌåÆ```\n    70ŌåÆ\n    71ŌåÆ- Beam starts at (0,1), moves to (1,1) ŌĆö hits splitter.\n    72ŌåÆ- Splits: down-left to (2,0) hits another splitter, down-right to (2,2) hits another splitter.\n    73ŌåÆ- (2,0) splitter: sends beams to (3,-1) absorbed and (3,1).\n    74ŌåÆ- (2,2) splitter: sends beams to (3,1) and (3,3).\n    75ŌåÆ- `countBeamCells`: (0,1), (1,1), (2,0), (2,2), (3,1), (3,3) ŌåÆ **6** (note: two beams land on (3,1) but it counts once).\n    76ŌåÆ- `countBeamPaths`: 4 paths total, but one is absorbed ŌåÆ **3n